        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-03-19 12:05:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI have no objection to the patch per se (although those functions don't exist on orion any more :( ), but i'm wondering whether glimpsing a group lock is a good idea actually. Several nodes can be handling the same GRP locks and i wonder how do we determine which ones will receive the GL AST? The server has no idea what node/process is actually the owner of the \"largest\" offset in the file.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
